@node "FREEWARE" "FREEware"

 I am releasing these objects as freeware because A) PARAMOUNT PICTURES may own
the right (I don't know if any of these have appeared in Star Trek) and B) This
is my way of giving back to all the other Amiga user that have written some
really cool programs.

 These objects are based on the plans in Eric Kristiansen's book "Jackill's Star
Fleet Reference Manual Ship's of the Fleet Volume III" (these are great tech
books (vol 1 through III) if you can get a hold of them).  

 tHE ARCHIVE CAN BE FREELY DISTRIBUTED AS LONG AS ALL FILES REMAIN INTACT. IF
YOU WANT TO CONVERT THEM INTO ANOTHER FORMAT, YOU MAY REPLACE THE OBJECTS, BUT
KEEP THIS GUIDE FILE AND ADD ANY INFORMATION NEEDED TO IT.  (IF YOU NEED AN
OTHER FORMAT @{"E-MAILĀME" link "author" 0} AND I WILL RUN THEM THROUGH PIXEL PRO AND SEND THEM TO
YOU). IF YOU INCLUDE IT ON A CD (EXCEPT THE AMINET) YOU MUST SEND ME A COPY OF
THE CD.

 STAR TREK IS A TRADE MARK OF PARAMOUNT PICTURES

 The specs on each buoy are taken from or based on "Jackill's Star Fleet
Reference Manual Ship's of the Fleet Volume III" (C) Eric Kristiansen 1995.
@endnode

@node "OverView" "OVERVIEW"

     These IMAGINE objects are based on the plans in Eric Kristiansen's book
"Jackill's Star Fleet Reference Manual Ship's of the Fleet Volume III" (these
are great tech books (vol 1 through III) if you can get a hold of them).  The
colors on the objects are my best guess [you may want to change the radar dish
to copper by changing the METALS2 in the attributes). What the heck are they?
They are communiction, marker, and defence buoys, use them to add detail to your
aminations (and they are great for target practice.)

 Objects' scale are 1 imagine unit equals 1 meter.
@endnode

@node "APB" "APPROACH POSITION BEACON"

 APB.ibj

 @{b}APPROACH POSITION BEACON@{ub}                                            APB-1/DC
 ============================================================================
 @{u}CLASSIFICATION@{uu}: APPROACH POSITION BEACON

 @{u}MODEL@{uu}: APB-1

 @{u}RANGE@{uu}: 6.80x10^13 km

 @{u}TELEMETRY/CHANNELS@{uu}: 78,521

 @{u}BUOY FEATURES@{uu}:
   standard package
   communication software
   electromagnetic sensors
   field detectors
   interstellar communication
   multi-frequency beacon
   ship analysis software
   subspace communication

 @{u}DESCRIPTION@{uu}:  buoys placed on the edge of solar systems and hazardous debris
fields to provide guidance information.

 @{u}TEXTURES@{uu}:RdSthStr,FireBall,Dirt (all standard Imagine textures)
@endnode

@node "CB" "COMMUNICATION BUOY"

 CB.ibj

 @{b}COMMUNICATION BUOY@{ub}                                                  CB-1/KK2
 ============================================================================
 @{u}CLASSIFICATION@{uu}: COMMUNICATION BUOY

 @{u}MODEL@{uu}: CB-1

 @{u}RANGE@{uu}: 1.42x10^14 km

 @{u}TELEMETRY/CHANNELS@{uu}: 202,153

 @{u}BUOY FEATURES@{uu}:
   standard package
   alpha sensor package
   communication software
   fempto second data collection
   high gain antenna
   interstellar communication
   multi-frequency beacon
   subspace communication

 @{u}DESCRIPTION@{uu}: Placed around planets or spread through out a solar system.
Provides sub-space communication for peripheral worlds and deep-space
facilities.  Includes Galactic time-base.

 @{u}TEXTURES@{uu}: Dirt, Metals2 (all standard Imagine textures)
@endnode

@node "CLY" "COLONY BUOY"

 CLY.ibj

 @{b}COLONY BUOY@{ub}                                                        CLY-1/PDS
 ============================================================================
 @{u}CLASSIFICATION@{uu}: COLONY BUOY

 @{u}MODEL@{uu}: CLY-1

 @{u}RANGE@{uu}: 5.48x10^13 km

 @{u}TELEMETRY/CHANNELS@{uu}: 16,234

 @{u}BUOY FEATURES@{uu}:
   standard package
   communication software
   electronic counter measure
   interstellar communication
   multi-frequency beacon
   subspace communication

 @{u}DESCRIPTION@{uu}: Usually these are put in orbit of a colony planet.  It provides
subspace communications, surveillance and sensor sweeps of the planet for survey
work.

 @{u}TEXTURES@{uu}: Dirt (standard Imagine texture)
@endnode

